{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17489503","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17489503"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T04:19:27+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T04:19:27+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"675"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"675","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/675"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.11,0.04,0.23,0.36,0.27]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"675"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"40293"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"675","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/675"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"675"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"25005"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"3464"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"617"},{"type":"contributions","id":"914"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18066"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"40293","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/40293"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn otherwise fit 37-year-old woman has an abdominal CT scan performed as part of long-term management of uterine fibroids. There is an incidental finding of a probable gastrointestinal stromal tumour (GIST). The lesion has a diameter of 6 cm, is well-defined and located almost entirely within the stomach (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Imatinib (tyrosine kinase inhibitor) chemotherapy","Sunitinib (tyrosine kinase inhibitor) chemotherapy","Endoscopic resection","Localised surgical resection","Subtotal gastrectomy"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EMost gastrointestinal stromal tumours are benign. In other words, this can be considered localised disease and the initial management plan should be local \u003Cstrong\u003Esurgical\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Cstrong\u003Eresection\u003C/strong\u003E. If this was a gastric cancer, then a subtotal gastrectomy would be appropriate. It is very unlikely that a gastric cancer would have got to this size without any symptoms (such as anorexia, early satiety and weight loss).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEndoscopic resection is inappropriate as the lesion is too large (\u0026gt;5cm), while a subtotal gastrectomy is not necessary for what is a relatively benign condition in most instances.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETyrosine kinase inhibitor therapy is used for more advanced disease \u2013 Imatinib for patients with metastatic or resectable c-KIT positive tumours, while Sunitinib is second-line therapy. However, it is often difficult to obtain a permanent cure with chemotherapy alone.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["An incidental finding is the commonest mode of \u2018presentation\u2019 for gastrointestinal stromal tumours."],"references":["von Mehren M, Joensuu H. Gastrointestinal Stromal Tumors. J Clin Oncol. 2018;36(2):136-143.","Akahoshi K, Oya M, Koga T, Shiratsuchi Y. Current clinical management of gastrointestinal stromal tumor. World J Gastroenterol. 2018;24(26):2806-2817.","Tan Y, Tan L, Lu J, Huo J, Liu D. Endoscopic resection of gastric gastrointestinal stromal tumors. Transl Gastroenterol Hepatol. 2017;2:115."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"25005"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"675"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"18448"}]},"explanationMedia":{"